The author, Deputy National Security Advisor Daleep Singh, shares his experience as an Indian American growing up in the United States. He discusses the challenges his parents faced in fitting in and the sacrifices they made for their family. Singh also reflects on his own struggles with identity and acceptance, including instances of racism and prejudice he faced as a child. He acknowledges the progress that has been made in terms of racial equality but emphasizes the need for continued efforts to address bias and privilege. Singh highlights his role in the Biden administration and his commitment to representing and advocating for the Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) community. He also expresses solidarity with the Sikh community, which has been targeted with harassment and violence in recent years.